.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-3-3::.
The people have 6 different jobs:  mechanic, architect, coach, pilot, paramedic, designer
The people use 6 different means of transport: subway, tram, jet-ski, roller, trike, skateboard
1. the person driving the roller is on the left or right of the mechanic##3
2. the paramedic is on the left of the person driving the subway##1
3. the mechanic is on the right of the person driving the tram##1
4. the coach is on the left or right of the person driving the tram##3
5. the person driving the roller is on the far right##1
6. the pilot is on the left or right of the person driving the jet-ski##3
7. the architect is between the pilot and the coach##2
8. the paramedic is on the right of the person driving the trike##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |     2      |      3      |     4     |    5     |     6     |
| Job         | pilot | architect | coach | paramedic | mechanic  | designer    |
| Transport   | skateboard      | jet-ski  | trike  | tram       | subway | roller |

